Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B ,=20
Happy Thursday!=20
This really will be the shortest Not Boring in history. You have a Memorial=
 Day Weekend to get to. But since odds are you=E2=80=99ll be in a car for a=
 couple hours at some point in the next few days, I thought it would be the=
 perfect time to listen to my favorite episode of Not Boring Founders yet.=20
Not Boring Founders is a twice-weekly podcast on which I talk to founders =
=E2=80=94 often Not Boring Capital portfolio founders =E2=80=94 about what =
the world looks like if they=E2=80=99re wildly successful, and how they=E2=
=80=99re making that version of the world a reality. =20
Normally, the episodes are about 30 minutes. For this one, with Replit [ ht=
tps://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEuOhSAQRVfzGBrlJw4Y9KS3QfhU-8hTMFh24u67=
1EEnhFAUtw73Ro8w13bare7Irs3huQGVKXq6OXZoLic7aG6EkhNLVqbBKMPy7n4awOrzYrEdwLY=
jLDl6zLXcir7nir0t96lXXPHEvRyjn0YaBT5qOpvgB_NA_ZEylAgWfqGdtQCLdV2h4DWKLfaNuO=
0v8fXi37QabEvGjp5QwbLlPecE0QNXkstOdNFIFUCHOIoYhIwv2a8z7_Yj7Ojj51KyZkvFUFsuM=
7U_b7_CcjfIiLvoR8l4Oig-LJAej_jkdLt2MxRolF9yHikgJZSe9GjMJB5P9HOltTCDGhiRUyVV=
-Yf-Ab9Af50 ] co-founder and CEO Amjad Masad [ https://email.mg2.substack.c=
om/c/eJxFkEtuxCAQRE8zLC3Mb_CCRTa5BuLT40FjgwXtRL59sL2IhFpqmqL6VXAIc6mH2UpDch=
aLxwa9jcH1m71BtSmaUTHNpZhINCKOWmqSmn1VgNWlxWDdgWy7X1JwmEq-FJQySd4mRBakiC_nJ=
UQ5AdXehZEq9uQxTFTfpm6PCXIAAz9Qj5KBhLKukPH8iizmjbi1B_96sO9-8DchQh36m9651TUX=
STKMMkYlUyOTgomBD0EL6UH58OTBcxEegq4zG9ruG7rwOfWkmlzQl5ry3Meft1thuQadx55L7Dn=
hYSE7v0C8UfGO64K3M2SoPcZoHfacJJdqUk-tJ36jdQCpFNejHEl3jqWr8r_pHzOdgvE ], we =
went a full 1 hour 41 minutes, covering a wide range of topics:
Decentralized software creation
How the internet could have been built differently=20
The history and future of coding (aka when Wordcels rule the code)
Amjad=E2=80=99s story: from Jordan to Codecademy, Facebook, and Replit
Authenticity Alpha=20
Balancing theory and just doing things=20
Replit=E2=80=99s hiring spree and talent density
The software economy being built on Replit
Aggressiveness vs. caution in the current market
I hate listening to myself talk, and I listened to this one all the way thr=
ough.=20
Amjad has quickly become one of my favorite people in tech, and is someone =
who I genuinely believe will play a big role in shaping the future. I belie=
ved that when I wrote about Replit in December, and I believe it even more =
strongly after this conversation.=20
You can listen to this episode right in this post =E2=80=94 just press play=
